%% Data Flow Diagram for Notebooks (Workbench Images)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant Konflux as Konflux Pipeline<br/>(Tekton)
    participant Git as Source Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PyPI as pypi.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Quay as quay.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant User as User (Browser)
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as ODH Notebook<br/>Controller
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Dev,Quay: Flow 1: Image Build and Deployment
        Dev->>Konflux: Trigger build
        Konflux->>Git: Clone source<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Git credentials
        Konflux->>Registry: Pull base image (UBI9)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Registry pull secret
        Konflux->>PyPI: Prefetch Python packages<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Hash-verified (pylock.toml)
        Konflux->>Quay: Push built image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Push credentials
        Operator->>Quay: Reference image digest<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>RELATED_IMAGE refs
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Deploy ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Workbench Launch
        User->>Dashboard: Select notebook image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>OpenShift OAuth
        Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount
        NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Pod + Service + HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull notebook image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull secret
        User->>Gateway: Access notebook<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>RBAC: Route request<br/>HTTPS/8443<br/>kube-rbac-proxy
        RBAC->>Notebook: Proxy authenticated request<br/>HTTP/8888, plaintext (localhost)
        Notebook-->>RBAC: Response
        RBAC-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: Notebook UI
    end
